  "chunk_index": 28,
  "summary": "Bobby and Frankie discuss the possibility that Dr. Nicholson’s death was not a suicide, despite Sylvia Baskington-French providing him with an alibi. Sylvia testified that when the gunshot rang out, Nicholson arrived from the driveway and led her to the study window, which would mean he could not have been the shooter. Bobby remains skeptical of the alibi, but he and Frankie decide to shift their investigation toward the Kemm family at 17 Paddington St. Leonard's Garden. To avoid recognition, Frankie plans to visit them while posing as a political lobbyist.\n\nThe conversation turns to Moira, whom Bobby believes is in grave danger. He suggests that Nicholson had two obstacles to remove before marrying Sylvia, and with Henry gone, Moira is the next target. Bobby proposes moving Moira to a castle in Wales for her safety. Frankie agrees and plans to drive to Granchester at 10:30 to find Molly.\n\nAfter saying goodbye to a pale and exhausted Roger at Merroway Manor, Frankie and Bobby drive to Granchester. Upon arriving at the oppressive, heavily bolted house, they are met by a nurse. Dr. Nicholson informs Frankie that Moira is in a very bad state and may not survive the night.",
